The paper discusses the use of neural networks for traffic flow forecasting, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on multitask learning (MTL) using backpropagation (BP) neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of computer vision techniques for traffic flow analysis, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the application of MTL to traffic flow forecasting, which could place it under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
